Problem Description

Given a string A and integer B, remove all consecutive same characters that have length exactly B.

Problem Constraints
1 <= |A| <= 100000

1 <= B <= |A|

Input Format
First Argument is string A.

Second argument is integer B.

Output Format
Return a string after doing the removals.

Example Input
Input 1:

A = "aabcd"
B = 2
Input 2:

A = "aabbccd"
B = 2

Example Output
Output 1:

 "bcd"
Output 2:

 "d"

Example Explanation
Explanation 1:

 "aa" had length 2.
Explanation 2:

 "aa", "bb" and "cc" had length of 2.
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 string Solution::solve(string A, int B) {
    if(B==1)    return "";
    int n = A.size();
    string ans = "";
    int i = 0;
    while(i<n)
    {
        int j = i+1;
        while(A[i]==A[j])
            j++;
        if(j-i<B)
        {
            ans = ans + A.substr(i,j-i);
        }
        i=j;
    }
    return ans;
}
